Empty ggplot

ggplot(data = linelist)

Add axis mappings

ggplot(data = linelist,
       mapping = aes(
         x = age,
         y = days_hosp))

A common error:

# create data
outcome_time_data <- linelist %>% 
  group_by(died,
           week_onset = lubridate::floor_date(date_onset, "week")) %>% 
  summarise(n_cases = n()) %>%

  select(week_onset, everything()) %>% 
  arrange(week_onset) %>% 
  drop_na(week_onset)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'died'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
# Show top
outcome_time_data %>%
  head() %>% 
  knitr::kable()
week_onset died n_cases
2019-12-29 Yes 1
2019-12-29 No 5
2020-01-05 No 7
2020-01-05 Unknown 1
2020-01-12 Yes 1
2020-01-12 No 5 
# plot with error
ggplot(
  data = outcome_time_data,
  mapping = aes(
    x = week_onset,       
    y = n_cases)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "Weekly cases, by outcome (?)")

# plot resolved
ggplot(
  data = outcome_time_data,
  mapping = aes(
    x = week_onset,       
    y = n_cases,
    color = died)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "Weekly cases, by outcome")

Facets/small multiples

# facet wrap by ethnicity/race value
ggplot(data = linelist,
       mapping = aes(x = date_onset)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_wrap(~ eth_race)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

# facet wrap with free y-axes
ggplot(data = linelist,
       mapping = aes(x = date_onset)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_wrap(~ eth_race, scales = "free_y") +
  labs(caption = "Note the free y-axis")

  data = linelist,
  mapping = aes(x = date_onset)) +
  geom_histogram() +

# drop levels you do not want
linelist %>% 
  drop_na(gender, eth_race) %>% 
  filter(gender != "Unknown") %>% 
  
  ggplot(
    mapping = aes(x = date_onset)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_grid(gender ~ eth_race)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.
## Warning: Removed 37016 rows containing non-finite values (stat_bin).

# facets with gghighlight and fill
ggplot(
  data = linelist,
  mapping = aes(
    x = date_onset,
    fill = eth_race)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_wrap(~ eth_race) +
  gghighlight::gghighlight()

gghighlight

# geom_line with gghighlight
linelist %>% 
  # get daily counts by zip code
  group_by(age_group, date_report) %>%
  count() %>% 
  
  # plot
  ggplot(
    mapping = aes(
      x = date_report,
      y = n,
      color = age_group)) +
  geom_line()+
  gghighlight::gghighlight(age_group %in% c("40-49", "60-69")) +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
